From: quark <quark@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] msctf: Tolerate WH_CBT focus hook failure

In environments where Wine's hook infrastructure is not fully wired
up (notably quark+triskelion on Wine 11.6), SetWindowsHookExW(WH_CBT)
can return NULL. The original code returned E_FAIL, but the caller
(ThreadMgr_AssociateFocus, ThreadMgr_ActivateEx) ignores the return
value, so msctf shipped a half-built ITfThreadMgr to SDL2 via
RoGetActivationFactory. SDL2 then dereferenced uninitialized focus
state and triggered STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION (c0000005), caught by
ntdll's user_callback_handler and silently swallowed — but the
calling thread's state was already corrupted, leading to downstream
crashes (Lua VM corruption in LOVE2D, etc.).

Fix: report success on hook failure. msctf works in degraded mode
without the focus hook — IME auto-focus tracking is disabled but
the rest of TSF works. This eliminates the c0000005 cascade and
returns a consistent (if reduced) ITfThreadMgr to the caller.

diff --git a/dlls/msctf/threadmgr.c b/dlls/msctf/threadmgr.c
index 11c79c0..9b29d9d 100644
--- a/dlls/msctf/threadmgr.c
+++ b/dlls/msctf/threadmgr.c
@@ -428,8 +428,16 @@ static HRESULT SetupWindowsHook(ThreadMgr *This)
                              GetCurrentThreadId());
         if (!This->focusHook)
         {
-            ERR("Unable to set focus hook\n");
-            return E_FAIL;
+            /* The CBT hook can fail in environments where Wine's hook
+             * infrastructure is not fully wired up. Returning E_FAIL here
+             * leaves the caller (and SDL2 via RoGetActivationFactory) with
+             * a half-built ITfThreadMgr whose focus state never updates,
+             * leading to NULL derefs caught as STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION by
+             * user_callback_handler. msctf works in degraded mode without
+             * the hook — IME focus changes simply aren't auto-tracked.
+             * Report success so the caller proceeds with consistent state. */
+            WARN("Unable to set focus hook - continuing in degraded mode\n");
+            return S_OK;
         }
         return S_OK;
     }
